The paper deals with image processing tasks such as denoising, rain streak removal, and super-resolution, which are all subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, specifically a GAN, to model noise in images, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which involves measuring performance metrics, indicating a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
